{
  "abstract": "There is global consensus that climate is changing mainly due to the anthropogenic\r\nemissions of green house gases (IPCC, 2007b). Also, there is a widespread concern\r\nover long-term climate changes and changes in climate variability through occurrence\r\nof extreme weather events such as cyclones, floods, droughts, sea level rise etc.\r\nAgriculture is exposed, directly and affected considerably by climate and its changes.\r\nDue to the spatially different impacts of climate change, there is a need to understand\r\nits context in each region with respect to exposure, expected impacts, vulnerability status\r\nand the response strategies to mitigate, core and adapt better with the process of climate\r\nchange................",
